<h2>Ideating</h2>
<p>To reference something unique about Wichita, I turned to our city's nickname, "The Air Capital of the World." Wichita experienced a boom in aerospace manufacturing factories in the late 1920s. Those factories have been a source of identity for our city ever since. Additionally, the Kansas State motto is "Ad Astra Per Aspera," which translates: "To the Stars, Through Difficulty." I decided to run with <em>outer space</em> as the theme.</p>

<p>Initially, I had trouble coming up with a visual concept. "Impact" recalls the image of a large object crashing into something else, leaving destruction in its wake. It all felt too violent and morbid. I ultimately decided to merely allude to an impact; instead of visualizing one outright. The subject became a meteorite flying through the earth's atmosphere, debris trail behind it, impact imminent. </p>

<h2>Iterating</h2>

<p>I began experimenting with different visual styles landed on something I liked. I wanted to see if any other frames made sense, and a circle felt best. The meteorite was looking lonely, so I gave it a few star friends. Fun fact: The four-pointed star shape is called an astroid.</p>

